Description: Fix CallableInfo::closure_native_address() return type
 gjs 1.86.0 declares GI::InfoOperations<...,CALLABLE>::closure_native_address()
 as returning void**, but the underlying gobject-introspection function
 gi_callable_info_get_closure_native_address() returns void*. Result:
     gi/info.h:887:59: error: invalid conversion from 'void*' to 'void**'
     [-fpermissive]
 .
 Upstream fix is GNOME/gjs MR !1057 (post-1.86.0). The MR also renames
 closure() -> get_func_ptr() across function.h, arg-cache.cpp, object.cpp,
 but those are cosmetic — the actual type-mismatch fix is the single-
 character change to the info.h declaration. With void** -> void*, the
 existing closure() wrapper returns void* (matching), and all consumers
 (function.h, arg-cache.cpp, object.cpp) which use the value as void*
 continue to work without modification.
Origin: upstream, https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gjs/-/merge_requests/1057 (subset)
Author: Philip Chimento <philip.chimento@gmail.com>

--- a/gi/info.h
+++ b/gi/info.h
@@ -883,7 +883,7 @@
         return gi_callable_info_can_throw_gerror(ptr());
     }
     [[nodiscard]]
-    void** closure_native_address(ffi_closure* closure) const {
+    void* closure_native_address(ffi_closure* closure) const {
         return gi_callable_info_get_closure_native_address(ptr(), closure);
     }
     [[nodiscard]]
